summary: This document is an email chain from April 23, 2020, discussing the review and tracking of FBI 302 interview reports (likely related to the Epstein case). The sender notes that the files are updated on a tracker and points out a couple of names that appear differently in the new 302s compared to existing files. The chain references a batch of interviews ending with a specific number (377).

events.title: Email exchange regarding FBI 302s
events.description: Email correspondence discussing the review and tracking of FBI 302 interview reports, noting duplicates and name discrepancies.

keyFacts: The document is an email chain dated April 23, 2020, concerning FBI 302 interview reports.
The sender notes that a couple of names appear differently in the new 302s compared to existing files, indicating potential discrepancies in witness or subject identification.
The email references a batch of interviews ending with the number 377, suggesting a specific set of investigative documents.
The correspondence indicates an ongoing process of updating and tracking investigative materials related to the Epstein case.
